cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM

The paper deals with video anomaly detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces new evaluation criteria and algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the limitations of current datasets, which may place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as anomaly detection is often used in security applications. Finally, the paper deals with video data, which may also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
